  "body": "This is a feature request. First I LOVE the react-hooks. There's one thing I'm thinking can we improve a little bit about the signature of `useEffect`.\r\nCurrent useEffect signature is:\r\n```javascript\r\nuseEffect(\r\n  create: () => (() => void) | void,\r\n  inputs: Array<mixed> | void | null,\r\n)\r\n```\r\nWhich I feel like it's not super obvious that the useEffect is actually dependent on the inputs sometimes. Because it's in the bottom and people might not notice it sometimes.\r\n\r\nI'm thinking do we want to support an alternative signature:\r\n```javascript\r\nuseEffect(\r\n  inputs: Array<mixed> | void | null,\r\n  create: () => (() => void) | void,\r\n)\r\n```\r\nSo when we write the code, it can be like:\r\n```javascript\r\nuseEffect(['dep1', 'dep2'], () => {\r\n});\r\n```\r\nIn this way, you just cannot ignore the dependencies.\r\n",
